    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="843"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1960a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1170. A note of this Government in regard to interference with neutral commerce
                    by British authorities has been sent to London, and I have asked Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1">Page</persName> to mail you a copy upon its delivery to
                    the British Government. Upon receipt of the copy, please transmit it to the
                    French Foreign Office for the information of the French Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
